*epix-1.1.17 (15 Sep 2007)

  15 Sep 2007; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org> +files/epix-1.1.17-doc-gentoo.patch, +epix-1.1.17.ebuild:
  Version bump. Thanks much to the maintainer Andrew D. Hwang
  <ahwang@mathcs.holycross.edu> for his efforts to making the epix
  install on gentoo even smoother!

  13 Sep 2007; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org>
  +files/50epix-gentoo.el:
  Added missing site file (fixes bug #192283).

  11 Sep 2007; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org> epix-1.1.15.ebuild:
  Moved emacs dependencies into DEPEND.

  11 Sep 2007; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org> epix-1.1.15.ebuild:
  Added emacs support (see bug #182056). Thanks much to
  <opfer@gentoo.org> for his patch.

*epix-1.1.15 (09 Sep 2007)

  09 Sep 2007; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org>
  +files/epix-1.1.15-doc-gentoo.patch, +epix-1.1.15.ebuild:
  Version bump (bug #191798).

  11 Jun 2007; Marcus D. Hanwell <cryos@gentoo.org> -epix-1.0.0.ebuild,
  -epix-1.0.20.ebuild, epix-1.0.24.ebuild:
  Marked stable on amd64, removed old versions.

*epix-1.0.24 (07 Apr 2007)

  07 Apr 2007; Marcus D. Hanwell <cryos@gentoo.org> +epix-1.0.24.ebuild:
  Version bump.

  22 Feb 2007; Markus Ullmann <jokey@gentoo.org> ChangeLog:
  Redigest for Manifest2

  18 Nov 2006; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org> epix-1.0.20.ebuild:
  Added logic to redirect all output to /dev/null to avoid problems
  in the sandbox.

*epix-1.0.20 (09 Nov 2006)

  09 Nov 2006; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org> +epix-1.0.20.ebuild:
  Version bump.

  29 Aug 2006; Tobias Scherbaum <dertobi123@gentoo.org> epix-1.0.7.ebuild:
  ppc stable, bug #144275

  28 Aug 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> epix-1.0.7.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64/x86 wrt bug #144275.

  24 Jun 2006; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org> epix-1.0.7.ebuild:
  Force MAKEOPTS="-j1" since the makefile breaks for parallel builds.
  This closes bugs #135266 and #137762.

  07 Jun 2006; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>
  files/epix-doc-gentoo.patch:
  Fixed the last fix - removing '-v' was not enough, adding '-q' helped.

  06 Jun 2006; Markus Dittrich <markusle@gentoo.org>
  files/epix-doc-gentoo.patch:
  Fix makefile patch to address sandbox issues when building the docs
  (see bug #135266).

